The paper discusses a novel blind multi-user detection framework for non-orthogonal multiple access, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The focus is on communication systems, particularly grant-free transmission, which falls under the category of communication (cs.COMM). The paper also discusses blind channel estimation and activation detection, which are related to signal processing (cs.SY) and machine learning (cs.LG).
